# GeoDesign Astro — standards (marketing site)

Use this file for **page-level and layout work** under `astro/`. For **React island** components, also follow [.cursor/rules/react_standards.mdc](./react_standards.mdc) where applicable.

## Goals

- **SEO:** Ship correct `<title>`, description, canonical, Open Graph, and structured data in the **initial HTML** for each route.
- **Lightweight:** Default to zero client JS; add React islands only with explicit `client:*` directives.

## Structure

- **Layouts:** Shared head + chrome in `astro/src/layouts/` (e.g. `BaseLayout.astro`).
- **Routes:** File-based under `astro/src/pages/`; use `404.astro` for not-found.
- **Styling:** Tailwind v4 via `@import "tailwindcss"` in `astro/src/styles/global.css`.

## Astro patterns

- Use `Astro.site` and `Astro.url` for canonical and absolute OG image URLs.
- Prefer **`.astro` components** for static sections; **React** only for interactivity.
- Do not add unnecessary `client:load` — prefer `client:visible` or `client:idle` for below-the-fold widgets.

## Accessibility

- Semantic landmarks (`header`, `main`, `nav`, `footer`), skip link, visible focus — align with WCAG 2.1 AA goals from the React standards doc.

## Security

- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` unless sanitized; prefer Astro-native content.
- External iframes (maps, video): `title` attribute and conservative `referrerpolicy` where relevant.

## Configuration

- **`site`** in `astro.config.mjs` must match production (`https://geodesign.co.in`) for sitemap and absolute URLs.
